{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> φθόνος</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>ill-will</b> or <b>malice,</b> especially <b>envy</b> or <b>jealousy</b> of the good fortune of others [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Definitiones” 416b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1387b22), 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 8.55, etc.; φθόνῳ \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>through envy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.30, 9.71 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to εὔνοια, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 635b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ἔπαινος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 24.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἴσχει ὄλβος φθόνον incurs <b>envy,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 11.29, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 5.68; φθόνον πρὸς ἀστῶν ἀλφάνουσι 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 297; φθόνῳ χρῆσθαι πρὸς τὰ παιδικά 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 253b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κρέσσων οἰκτιρμοῦ φθόνος better <b>to be envied</b> than pitied ! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.85, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.6; πρὸς γὰρ τὸν ἔχονθ᾽ ὁ φ. ἕρπει 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 157 (_anapaest meter_), compare “OT” 382; ἐς τἀπίσημα δ᾽ ὁ φ. πηδᾶν φιλεῖ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 294 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φ. συνεστιώμενος, of wealth, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Secundus Gnomologus “Sententiae - FPG” 9; φ. [ἐστὶ] τοῖς ζῶσι πρὸς τὸ ἀντίπαλον 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.45; κατὰ φθόνον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 686, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 457d; σὺν φθόνῳ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 780 (Lyric poetry); διὰ φθόνον NT.Phil.1.15 \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> objecti, <b>envy for, jealousy of,</b> τῶν πεπραγμένων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 2.48 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; φθόνον δὲ σωμάτων ἕξει θεός i.e. <b>will grudge, deny,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 859 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> <i>subjunctive</i>, <b>envy</b> or <b>jealousy felt by</b> another, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Hp.Ma.” 282a; also φ. ἐφ᾽ ἑτέροις 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.39e, etc.; εἴς τινα “Anthologia Graeca” 6.257 (1st c.AD: Antiphilus Epigrammaticus); πρός τινα 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Rh.Pr.” 22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, <b>envyings, jealousies, heartburnings,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 15.163, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 679c, 801e, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> a <b>cause for indignation,</b> a <b>reproach,</b> ἀποκτείνειν φθόνος [ἐστὶ] γυναῖκας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 288. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> especially <b>jealousy</b> of the gods [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare (φθονερός 1.2), θεῶν φ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 362, “Ag.” 947; φ. μὴ γένοιτό τις θεῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 1135: hence _absolutely_, τὸν φ. δὲ πρόσκυσον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 776; εὐλαβούμενος φθόνον 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.305. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>refusal from feelings of ill-will</b> or <b>envy, grudging,</b> φθόνος μὲν οὐδεὶς.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 628 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; οὐδεὶς φ. or φ. οὐδείς, with <i>infinitive</i>, said in granting a request willingly, ἃ τυγχάνω ἀκηκοώς, φ. οὐδεὶς λέγειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 61d; οὐδεὶς.. φ. αὐτῷ διελθεῖν αὐτά [prev. author] “Sph.” 217a, compare b. “Lg.” 641d, 664a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5355","accentedUnicode":"φθόνος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5354","matchingForm":"φθονέω","stepTransliteration":"fthoneō","gloss":"to envy","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"envidiar","_zh_Gloss":"嫉妒"}],"shortDef":"envy","mediumDef":"<b>envy, jealously, spite,</b> <ref='Mat.27.18'>Mt. 27:18</ref>; <ref='Mrk.15.10'>Mk. 15:10</ref>; <ref='Rom.1.29'>Rom. 1:29;</ref> <ref='Gal.5.21'>Gal. 5:21;</ref> <ref='Php.1.15'>Phil. 1:15;</ref> <ref='1Ti.6.4'>1Tim. 6:4;</ref> <ref='Tit.3.3'>Tit. 3:3;</ref> <ref='Jas.4.5'>Jas. 4:5;</ref> <ref='1Pe.2.1'>1Pet. 2:1</ref>*","stepGloss":"envy","stepTransliteration":"fthonos","count":9,"_es_Definition":"envidia, celos, rencor","_zh_tw_Definition":"嫉妒","_zh_Definition":"嫉妒","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự ganh tị","_zh_tw_Gloss":"嫉妒","_es_Gloss":"envidia","_zh_Gloss":"嫉妒"}]}